to vote. But also voting on a merger is slightly more salient than voting o=
n a necessary extension to complete that merger. =E2=80=9CDo you want $54.2=
0=E2=80=9D is a simple question; =E2=80=9Cdo you want to delay a year to ha=
ve a good chance of getting $25-ish of value rather than getting $10.20 nex=
t week=E2=80=9D is more confusing.


  [2] See section 8.1(b)(iii) of  the merger agreement, which unlike some o=
f Musk=E2=80=99s other termination rights is not qualified by the requireme=
nt that *he* not be in breach of his obligations.


  [3] The link in that sentence goes to Twitter=E2=80=99s merger proxy, whi=
ch lists Vanguard Group as the biggest shareholder, a footnote cites to an =
April 8 Vanguard filing for Vanguard=E2=80=99s holdings. Bloomberg=E2=80=99=
s HDS page shows Vanguard disposing of some shares after that filing but be=
fore the record date for the Twitter meeting, leaving Musk as the biggest s=
hareholder. Either way it=E2=80=99s close though.


