<h2 style=3D"font-weight: bold; font-family: &quot;Arial Black&quot;, Arial=
, Helvetica, sans-serif; letter-spacing: -1px; font-size: 20px; border-bott=
om-width: 1px; border-bottom-style: dotted; margin: 0px; padding: 16px 0px =
5px;">Twitter vote</h2>
</td>
</tr>
</table>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">Twitter Inc.=E2=80=99s shareholders are voting=
 today on whether to sell the company=C2=A0to Elon Musk at $54.20 per share=
. Twitter closed yesterday at $41.41 per share. There is not much suspense =
here. If you have stock that is worth $41.41 per share, and someone wants t=
o buy it from you at $54.20, you should let him. Twitter is easily going to=
 get its votes.<a class=3D"footnote-index" href=3D"#footnote-1" style=3D"co=
lor: #000000; text-decoration: none !important; border-bottom-width: 1px; b=
order-bottom-color: #000000; border-bottom-style: none !important; backgrou=
nd-color: transparent !important; display: inline-block;">
<span>[1]</span>
</a>=C2=A0The <a href=3D"https://link.mail.bloombergbusiness.com/click/2903=
8310.263540/aHR0cHM6Ly93d3cud3NqLmNvbS9hcnRpY2xlcy90d2l0dGVyLXNoYXJlaG9sZGV=
ycy1hcmUtcG9pc2VkLXRvLWFwcHJvdmUtZWxvbi1tdXNrLXRha2VvdmVyLWRlYWwtMTE2NjMwMT=
Y3OTc/607f07ceef4b8524a319a23cBcefa9a17" itemprop=3D"StoryLink" itemscope=
=3D"itemscope" target=3D"_blank" style=3D"color: #000000; text-decoration: =
none !important; border-bottom-width: 1px; border-bottom-color: #000000; bo=
rder-bottom-style: solid; background-color: #ccc;"> Wall Street Journal rep=
orts</a>:</p>
<blockquote><p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">Early votes show investors approvi=
ng the deal by a wide margin, the people said, though there is always a cha=
nce that the results could change as shareholders can alter their votes thr=
ough a meeting scheduled for Tuesday at 1 p.m. Eastern time.</p></blockquot=
e>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">I do not actually think there=E2=80=99s much c=
hance that the results could change. If you are a Twitter shareholder, what=
 could possibly happen between now and 1 p.m. that would make you=C2=A0<em>=
not=C2=A0</em>want to cash out at $54.20?</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">There are a few complications. One is that new=
s is definitely happening about Twitter today. Peiter =E2=80=9CMudge=E2=80=
=9D Zatko, Twitter=E2=80=99s former head of security who has turned whistle=
-blower, <a href=3D"https://link.mail.bloombergbusiness.com/click/29038310.=
263540/aHR0cHM6Ly93d3cuYmxvb21iZXJnLmNvbS9uZXdzL2FydGljbGVzLzIwMjItMDktMTMv=
dHdpdHRlci1nZXRzLW9uZS10d28tcHVuY2gtYXMtd2hpc3RsZS1ibG93ZXItcGlsZXMtb24tYWZ=
0ZXItbXVzaz9jbXBpZD1CQkQwOTEzMjJfTU9ORVlTVFVGRiZ1dG1fbWVkaXVtPWVtYWlsJnV0bV=
9zb3VyY2U9bmV3c2xldHRlciZ1dG1fdGVybT0yMjA5MTMmdXRtX2NhbXBhaWduPW1vbmV5c3R1Z=
mY/607f07ceef4b8524a319a23cBc186bee6" itemprop=3D"StoryLink" itemscope=3D"i=
temscope" target=3D"_blank" style=3D"color: #000000; text-decoration: none =
!important; border-bottom-width: 1px; border-bottom-color: #000000; border-=
bottom-style: solid; background-color: #ccc;">testified in Congress</a>=C2=
=A0today about how bad Twitter=E2=80=99s security=C2=A0is. But nothing that=
 he says is going to make Twitter shareholders=C2=A0<em>less=C2=A0</em>like=
ly to vote for the deal. The worse Twitter is, the more excited you should =
be about getting $54.20 for your Twitter shares. If Zatko showed up at this=
 hearing and said =E2=80=9Cactually Twitter=E2=80=99s security is great and=
 they=E2=80=99ve discovered cold fusion=E2=80=9D then I guess you should vo=
te to keep your shares; in a world where Twitter is worth much more than $5=
4.20 on its own, the vote will probably fail. But he didn=E2=80=99t say tha=
t.</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">Another complication is that, of course, votin=
g to sell to Musk at $54.20 doesn=E2=80=99t mean it=E2=80=99ll actually hap=
pen. Musk has terminated the deal (<a href=3D"https://link.mail.bloombergbu=
siness.com/click/29038310.263540/aHR0cHM6Ly93d3cuYmxvb21iZXJnLmNvbS9vcGluaW=
9uL2FydGljbGVzLzIwMjItMDktMTIvY2l0aS1nb3QtaXRzLTUwMC1taWxsaW9uLWJhY2s_Y21wa=
WQ9QkJEMDkxMzIyX01PTkVZU1RVRkYmdXRtX21lZGl1bT1lbWFpbCZ1dG1fc291cmNlPW5ld3Ns=
ZXR0ZXImdXRtX3Rlcm09MjIwOTEzJnV0bV9jYW1wYWlnbj1tb25leXN0dWZm/607f07ceef4b85=
24a319a23cB785df11d" itemprop=3D"StoryLink" itemscope=3D"itemscope" target=
=3D"_blank" style=3D"color: #000000; text-decoration: none !important; bord=
er-bottom-width: 1px; border-bottom-color: #000000; border-bottom-style: so=
lid; background-color: #ccc;">three times!</a>) because he claims that Twit=
ter has breached some conditions and so he doesn=E2=80=99t have to actually=
 buy it; a Delaware court will decide if he=E2=80=99s right about any of th=
ose things. I tend to think that he=E2=80=99s wrong and will have to close,=
 but I don=E2=80=99t have especially huge confidence in that belief, and th=
e market-implied odds aren=E2=80=99t that great, which is why the stock is =
trading at $41.41. Still, if you are a Twitter shareholder, you have to vot=
e yes on the deal, because if everyone votes no then the deal is=C2=A0<em>d=
efinitely=C2=A0</em>dead; if shareholders don=E2=80=99t approve the deal, t=
hat gives Musk a fourth and unassailable reason for terminating it.<a class=
=3D"footnote-index" href=3D"#footnote-2" style=3D"color: #000000; text-deco=
ration: none !important; border-bottom-width: 1px; border-bottom-color: #00=
0000; border-bottom-style: none !important; background-color: transparent !=
important; display: inline-block;">
<span>[2]</span>
</a>=C2=A0The shareholders voting to close the deal is a necessary but not =
sufficient condition to the deal closing. Which is why they=E2=80=99ll vote=
 yes.</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">A third complication is that Twitter=E2=80=99s=
 <a href=3D"https://link.mail.bloombergbusiness.com/click/29038310.263540/a=
HR0cHM6Ly93d3cuc2VjLmdvdi9BcmNoaXZlcy9lZGdhci9kYXRhLzE0MTgwOTEvMDAwMTE5MzEy=
NTIyMjAyMTYzL2QyODMxMTlkZGVmbTE0YS5odG0jdG9jMjgzMTE5Xzkw/607f07ceef4b8524a3=
19a23cBa5fd7795" itemprop=3D"StoryLink" itemscope=3D"itemscope" target=3D"_=
blank" style=3D"color: #000000; text-decoration: none !important; border-bo=
ttom-width: 1px; border-bottom-color: #000000; border-bottom-style: solid; =
background-color: #ccc;"> biggest shareholder</a> is, uh, Elon Musk,<a clas=
s=3D"footnote-index" href=3D"#footnote-3" style=3D"color: #000000; text-dec=
oration: none !important; border-bottom-width: 1px; border-bottom-color: #0=
00000; border-bottom-style: none !important; background-color: transparent =
!important; display: inline-block;">
<span>[3]</span>
</a>=C2=A0and he=E2=80=99s trying to get out of the deal. Could he vote his=
 9.5% stake in Twitter <em>against=C2=A0</em>the deal, thus preventing it f=
rom closing? Well. The merger agreement (<a href=3D"https://link.mail.bloom=
bergbusiness.com/click/29038310.263540/aHR0cHM6Ly93d3cuc2VjLmdvdi9BcmNoaXZl=
cy9lZGdhci9kYXRhLzE0MTgwOTEvMDAwMTE5MzEyNTIyMjAyMTYzL2QyODMxMTlkZGVmbTE0YS5=
odG0jYW54YXRvYzI4MzExOV81Nw/607f07ceef4b8524a319a23cBc2f6550a" itemprop=3D"=
StoryLink" itemscope=3D"itemscope" target=3D"_blank" style=3D"color: #00000=
0; text-decoration: none !important; border-bottom-width: 1px; border-botto=
m-color: #000000; border-bottom-style: solid; background-color: #ccc;">sect=
ion 6.2(d)</a>) says that he has to vote in favor of the deal, but he claim=
s to have terminated the agreement (three times!) so perhaps he no longer f=
eels bound by that, and it is a bit awkward for him to vote yes on a deal t=
hat he wants to get out of. What will he do? Eh, it doesn=E2=80=99t really =
matter; I=E2=80=99m pretty sure that Twitter is going to get a huge majorit=
y and won=E2=80=99t actually need Musk=E2=80=99s votes.</p>
