 !important; border-bottom-width: 1px; border-bottom-color: #000000; border=
-bottom-style: solid; background-color: #ccc;">  announced</a> that Sam Ban=
kman-Fried=E2=80=99s FTX Ventures would acquire 30% of SkyBridge; the deal =
apparently also includes an option for FTX to buy 85% of SkyBridge. From th=
e outside it is not hard to guess at the motivations of the principals. Ban=
kman-Fried has lots of money and has been an opportunistic acquirer in a cr=
ypto bear market; buying SkyBridge presumably gives him some more mainstrea=
m distribution for crypto products. Scaramucci has had a rough year and nee=
ds the money; <a href=3D"https://link.mail.bloombergbusiness.com/click/2903=
8310.263540/aHR0cHM6Ly93d3cuZnQuY29tL2NvbnRlbnQvNTc0MDczODktYTRjNi00ZDkzLTk=
xYzQtMDE0ODUzNzQ4NTQw/607f07ceef4b8524a319a23cB85cbe327" itemprop=3D"StoryL=
ink" itemscope=3D"itemscope" target=3D"_blank" style=3D"color: #000000; tex=
t-decoration: none !important; border-bottom-width: 1px; border-bottom-colo=
r: #000000; border-bottom-style: solid; background-color: #ccc;"> the Finan=
cial Times reports</a>:</p>
<blockquote>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">Scaramucci said that the FTX deal was a produc=
t of poor performance in a poor market. SkyBridge, which has $2.8bn in asse=
ts under management, is down 25 per cent this year, he said.</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">=E2=80=9CBear markets suck,=E2=80=9D he added.=
 =E2=80=9CIf I was doing super-well right now =E2=80=94 our performance is =
mediocre, lacklustre =E2=80=94 who knows if we would be doing the transacti=
on.=E2=80=9D</p>
</blockquote>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">But there was also another motivation. The FT =
article goes on:</p>
<blockquote>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">Scaramucci said the transaction was decided ov=
er a two-hour lunch at a hotel in the Bahamas, where Bankman-Fried is based=
. Scaramucci was with his family on a Disney cruise that had docked in the =
islands.</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">He said he proposed lunch to discuss the possi=
bility of a partnership, as well as to avoid going to a water park with his=
 children.</p>
</blockquote>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">What percentage of mergers and acquisitions do=
 you think are driven by people trying to avoid spending time with their ch=
ildren?=C2=A0</p>
